        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 9:44PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 944 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Springer, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of South Central Colfax and Northeastern Mora
Counties.

This includes Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 400 and 408.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
